{"TopicId":202980,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Most Powerful Scifi Laser In Theory We Could Make","CreatedByName":"Spacescifi","CreatedById":197504,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-10T23:41:22Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Spacescifi","CreatedById":197504,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-10T23:41:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScenario: There is virtually no limit to how much energy you can pump into the beam....so long the laser itself or the laser focusing lens is not destroyed in the process. The problem is we are using only known materials and they ALL have thermal limits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuestion: I am guessing that the materials limits will probably be similar to nuclear thermal rocketry engine limits or less....right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaser lenses can be destroyed with too much heat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever I have read that lasers can self focus via plasma.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-focusing#:~:text=Ponderomotive%20self-focusing%20is%20caused,and%20inducing%20a%20focusing%20effect.\u0026amp;text=Self-focusing%20in%20a%20plasma,and%20channel%20a%20laser%20beam.\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-focusing#:~:text=Ponderomotive self-focusing is caused,and inducing a focusing effect.\u0026amp;text=Self-focusing in a plasma,and channel a laser beam.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo with advanced plasma setup instead of a glass lens, perhaps the laser power level could be pushed up even higher?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed I think all scifi lasers with uber power enough to cut through steel or burn through rock easily would benefiy from plasma focusing rather than a breakable glass lens.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-06-10T23:42:19Z\u0022 title=\u002206/10/2021 11:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJune 10, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Spacescifi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-10T23:54:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Nicoll#Nicoll-Dyson_Laser\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Nicoll#Nicoll-Dyson_Laser\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr a Stellaser per:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/0Ap4JhPoPQY?start=1280\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-11T00:23:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow about a stellar-pumped laser?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom the wiki page about\u00A0\u003Cem\u003EThe Ringworld Engineers\u003C/em\u003E, by Larry Niven:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#202122;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EThe control room contains living space and, among other things, the meteor defense system. The defense system uses the superconductor grid embedded in the Ringworld\u0027s\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ci style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#202122;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scrith\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0645ad;\u0022 title=\u0022Scrith\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Escrith\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/i\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#202122;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Efloor to manipulate the magnetic field of the Ringworld\u0027s sun to trigger\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_flare\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0645ad;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Solar flare\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Estellar flares\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#202122;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Ethat power a titanic\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laser#Gas_lasers\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0645ad;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Laser\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Egas laser\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#202122;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E. (The first expedition to the Ringworld crashed after being hit by this laser.)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-11T04:10:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs big as Cepheus A.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.3847/1538-4357/aab096\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.3847/1538-4357/aab096\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceFace545","CreatedById":196943,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-11T04:31:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u2019t know, it\u2019s sci fi so I\u2019d say it can be as powerful as the writer needs it to be\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spacescifi","CreatedById":197504,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-13T19:17:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me rephrase the question.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe most powerful laser you could put in theory on a spaceship?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tend to think lens size increases range, so I envision some wide radius plasma lens since plasma does not burn unlike glass lens.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SOXBLOX","CreatedById":204106,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-13T20:14:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuild a Shkadov thruster. Call it a ship. Occasionally dump collected solar energy into a Dyson laser. \u003Ci\u003EVoil\u00E1!\u003C/i\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen name the ship the\u00A0\u003Cem\u003EFiat Lux\u003C/em\u003E.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022^_^\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022^_^\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-06-13T20:15:47Z\u0022 title=\u002206/13/2021 08:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJune 13, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by SOXBLOX\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceFace545","CreatedById":196943,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-14T12:06:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223988665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022202980\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221623611847\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197504\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spacescifi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, Spacescifi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me rephrase the question.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe most powerful laser you could put in theory on a spaceship?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tend to think lens size increases range, so I envision some wide radius plasma lens since plasma does not burn unlike glass lens.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ultra mega quadrillion googolplex infinity quadcore laser focused laser\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-14T13:30:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs that\u00A0greater than three thousand?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-14T13:46:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223988935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022202980\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221623677403\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs that\u00A0greater than three thousand?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s over nine thousand.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}